bug.short_desc: pointer branch: scrolling lists with touch gesture lacks a pointerout event

long_desc.thetext:
We've some listitems that are sensible for the "hovered" state. That works fine so far if you use the mouse.
If you're using a touch device and scroll the list, the "hovered" state is not removed because the pointerout event has not been emitted.
Just checked it and it seems to work for me. Could you check the newest version pointer branch / master (we will merge any time soon).
The problem is still there. If I patch the code and remove the "hovered" state manually on pointerup, it works.
Could you supply a sample for me to reproduce?

Sure: http://tinyurl.com/nny5pqr
Note that it works in the playground version that you've deployed (it's rather old). You need the current pointer branch's playground to reproduce this.

Found a bug in the pointer handling. On touch devices, the spec demands a firing of pointerout after a pointerup. We already had that but not on the initial target. Changing the target fixed the issue.
